This is Aruru — multi-tenant SaaS for ceramic studios.
Named after the Sumerian goddess Aruru, she who shaped life from clay.

NEVER confuse with Calmi Experiments (different project, different repo).

Stack: FastAPI + MongoDB Atlas + React Native (Expo) + Vercel
Auth: JWT with { user_id, tenant_id, role }
Roles per studio: owner | assistant | member (NOT per user)
DB: MongoDB Atlas Frankfurt (eu-central-1)
GitHub org: przemyslawgolebiewski4-maker
Repos: aruru-app (this) | aruru-backend (FastAPI)

Design: src/theme/tokens.ts — always use tokens, never hardcode colours
Colors: clay #C4714A · moss #4A5E3A · cream #F7F3ED · ink #1E1A16
Fonts: DM Serif Display + Instrument Sans + DM Mono
UI: neurodivergent-friendly — calm, predictable, 0.5px borders

Key rule: users are GLOBAL (one email = one account everywhere).
Role lives in studio_members collection, not in users.
Every DB query must include tenant_id filter — enforced by middleware.

Current sprint: Sprint 1 — auth + tenant + role foundation
Active repo: aruru-backend (FastAPI, to be created)
